Hello,

I'm not a lawyer, and those licencing problems are just a nightmare to me !

http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-faq.html#AllCompatibility

This is a pain. I used first gplV3 because of fear of DRM problems that 
could occur with gplV2 to protect myself. And never to make trouble to 
anyone else, or to prevent the use of the code. Even if I read the full 
GPL licence, I have to admit that I don't understand all what it means. 
That's bad, I know.

I understand your concerns.

For now, please feel free to use it inside your module, with my written 
permission. I will think about releasing it to "gpl v2 or later" or any 
other licence that would make anybody happy... Is that fine for you ?

Nicolas

